The paper discusses the use of deep learning and deep reinforcement learning, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also emphasizes the use of evolutionary algorithms, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The discussion of the potential for application to a number of research areas suggests a broad scope, which could be associated with sub-categories such as cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
